prompt:
Add a public enum called Priority to Enums.calr, and then add an extension method IsUrgent that checks if the priority is High or Critical.

Use this exact Calor enum extension syntax:
§EN{e001:Priority:pub}
  Low
  Medium
  High
  Critical
§/EN{e001}

§EEXT{x001:Priority:pub}
  §MT{m001:IsUrgent:pub}
    §O{bool}
    §R (or (== this Priority.High) (== this Priority.Critical))
  §/MT{m001}
§/EEXT{x001}

The §EEXT{id:enumName:visibility} syntax creates enum extensions:
- id is the extension identifier
- enumName is the enum being extended
- 'this' refers to the enum value being extended
- Enables adding methods to enums
